{
  "texts": [
    "The same happens for the agent trained in hot climate, whose reward is worst in its own climate than in the rest.",
    "As a summary, Table 5 gathers the results obtained for each SAC training and evaluation combination in 5ZoneAutoDXVAV, which we will further discuss in Sect. 6.2.",
    "Another objective proposed in this work is to address the application of sequential learning: an approach that involves the progressive training of an agent under different weather conditions.",
    "On this basis, our goal in applying this incremental learning is to verify whether an agent trained progressively through different environments is capable of achieving better, or at least similar, performance to an agent trained in a single problem.",
    "Thus, based on the results obtained in Sect. 5.3, we will test to compare the performance of an agent directly trained on a single climate with one trained on every available climate."
  ]
}